☁️ AWS Services Used 
1️⃣ 🖥️ Amazon EC2
👉 What it does:
Hosts your Node.js microservices (payment, account, etc.)
👉 Why used:
You need a server to run backend code
Easily scalable (can increase instances during high traffic)
Full control over environment

2️⃣ 🌐 Amazon API Gateway
👉 What it does:
Entry point for all frontend requests
👉 Why used:
Routes requests to correct service
Provides security (authentication, throttling)
Prevents direct access to backend

3️⃣ 🗄️ Amazon RDS
👉 What it does:
Stores structured data:
Accounts
Transactions
User details
👉 Why used:
Reliable and managed database
Automatic backups
Handles financial data safely

4️⃣ ⚡ Amazon ElastiCache
👉 What it does:
Stores frequently used data in memory (Redis)
👉 Why used:
Faster response time
Reduces database load
Useful for:
Balance checks
Session storage

5️⃣ 📊 Amazon CloudWatch
👉 What it does:
Monitors logs and system performance
👉 Why used:
Detect failures (e.g., payment errors)
Tracks system health
Sends alerts
